{
  "body": "in [Variables](https://docs.perl6.org/language/variables)\r\n\r\n> The ^ twigil declares a formal positional parameter to blocks or subroutines.\r\n\r\nThe example includes the use of a different `^`:\r\n\r\n\tfor ^4 {\r\n\t\tsay \"$^b follows $^a\";\r\n\t}\r\n\r\nI think it would be less confusing to the newbie to see only one type of `^` in that example.",
